p</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A stopping time with respect to some filtration `f` is a function\n`τ` such that for all `i`, the preimage of `{j | j ≤ i}` along `τ` is measurable\nwith respect to `f i`.\n\nIntuitively, the stopping time `τ` describes some stopping rule such that at time\n`i`, we may determine it with the information we have at time `i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.html#MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime","kind":"def","line":69,"name":"MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.lean#L69-L76"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Probability.Process.Adapted","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Constructions.BorelSpace.WithTop","Mathlib.Data.ENat.Lattice"],"instances":[{"className":"MeasureTheory.SigmaFinite","name":"MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime.sigmaFinite_stopping_time","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.trim"]},{"className":"MeasureTheory.SigmaFinite","name":"MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime.sigmaFinite_stopping_time_of_le","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.trim"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Probability.Process.Stopping"}